edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.meta.parameters

Enum ParameterType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ParameterType>
      • edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.meta.parameters.ParameterType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ParameterType>

    public enum ParameterType
extends java.lang.Enum<ParameterType>
    Parameters for storage in a ParameterDictionary can be one of four types: boolean, integer, floating-point, or String. ParameterType specifies these and handles converting their names to strings.
    Author:
    Colin J. Fuller
